1.10
log
@Simplify fork/vfork logic: the kernel has handled returning zero in the child
for a long time, so there's no need to test the second return register here
in the asm stub.

ok and testing of many archs by krw@@ miod@@
@
text
@d1 1
a1 1
/*	$OpenBSD: Ovfork.S,v 1.9 2013/01/11 21:23:24 miod Exp $	*/
d38 1
a38 1
RSYSCALL(vfork)
@


1.9
log
@Add END() directives to the various functions.
Make the code PIC-aware when necessary (i.e. invoke other functions through
the PLT, and access global data through the GOT). No change for non-PIC
compilation.
@
text
@d1 1
a1 1
/*	$OpenBSD: Ovfork.S,v 1.8 2013/01/05 11:20:55 miod Exp $	*/
d38 1
a38 9
/* r2 = pid. r3 = 0 in parent, 1 in child */

SYSCALL(vfork)
	bcnd	eq0,%r3,parent
	or	%r2,%r0,0
	or	%r3,%r0,0
parent:
	jmp	%r1		/* pid = vfork() */
END(vfork)
@


